BFN 

<F P=106> [Communique issued by the Ningxia Hui Autonomous Region </F>
Statistics Bureau; date not given: "Statistical Report Issued 
by the Ningxia Hui Autonomous Region Statistics Bureau on 
National Economic and Social Development in 1993"] 
  [Text] In 1993, under the correct leadership of the CPC 
committee and the people's government of the Ningxia Hui 
Autonomous Region, people of various nationalities in the region 
seriously implemented the spirit of the 14th CPC Congress and 
the Third Plenary Session of the 14th CPC Central Committee, 
carried out in-depth reforms, expanded opening-up, seized the 
opportune moment, and quickened development. Macroeconomic 
environment, social supply, and demand relations were improved, 
and the national economy and social undertakings in the whole 
region achieved remarkable success. 
  In the whole year, the gross domestic product (GDP) was 9.65 
billion yuan, an increase of 10 percent over the previous year, 
of which the added value of primary industry (agriculture) 
amounted to 2.03 billion yuan, an increase of 5.5 percent; the 
added value of secondary industry (industry and building 
industry) amounted to 4.5 billion yuan, an increase of 12.9 
percent, in which industry amounted to 3.65 billion yuan, up 
12.8 percent, and building industry amounted to 850 million 
yuan, up 13.3 percent; and the added value of tertiary industry 
amounted to 3.12 billion yuan, an increase of 9.5 percent. 
Industrial structure was further optimized, and the structure 
ratio of tertiary industry was changed from 27.6:41.5:30.9 in 
1990 to 21.1:46.6:32.3. Per capita GDP was 1,965 yuan, an 
increase of 320 yuan over the previous year, up 19 percent. 
<H5>  I. Agriculture </H5>
  In 1993 the autonomous region further strengthened 
leadership 
over agriculture and rural work, intensified the foundation 
position of agriculture, quickened the pace of rural reforms, 
and constantly built and improved the agricultural socialized 
service system. Varied measures were taken to reduce the 
peasants' burdens, which resulted in an overall agricultural 
bumper harvest and sustained development of the rural economy. 
Total agricultural output reached 3.19 billion yuan, an 
increase of 6.7 percent over 1992, of which farming output 
amounted to 2.27 billion yuan, up by 9.8 percent; animal 
husbandry output amounted to 750 million yuan, up by 5.2 
percent; fishery output amounted to 80 million yuan, up by 12 
percent. 
  Agricultural production further entered a new stage. With 
the restructuring of the growing of crops, areas sown with 
refined strains of seeds were enlarged, and the output of most 
of the crops went up except for the reduction of paddy rice 
output due to the impact of low temperatures. Total grain 
output in the whole region broke the 2-million-ton record, and 
reached an all-time high of 2.03 million tons, of which summer 
crops amounted to 945,000 tons, up 28.3 percent, and autumn 
crops amounted to 1.085 million tons, down 3.1 percent. 


