  There was sustained growth in fishery production. The annual 
output of aquatic products totalled 15,000 tons, an increase of 
12.4 percent over that of the previous year. 
  The conditions of agricultural production continued to 
improve. At the end of 1993, the total power of agricultural 
machines in the whole region amounted to 2.176 million 
kilowatts, up 2.6 percent. The region had 5,000 large and 
medium-sized tractors, down 14 percent; 105,000 baby and hand 
tractors, up 5.1 percent; 4,000 trucks for agricultural use, 
even with the previous year; and power-driven irrigation and 
drainage machines with power amounting to 142,000 kilowatts, 
even with the previous year. As a result of the big increase in 
the prices of agricultural means of production, the amount of 
chemical fertilizer and electricity used for agriculture was 
reduced. The annual amount (conversion net) of chemical 
fertilizer applied totalled 134,000 tons, down 2.2 percent; and 
the amount of electricity used in the rural areas totalled 480 
million kwh, down 1.9 percent. The construction of water 
conservancy work was strengthened, and newly increased effective 
area under irrigation amounted to 103,000 mu. 
  There was an overall development of township and town 
enterprises in rural areas. In 1993, the total output of 
township and town enterprises in the whole region reached 3.06 
billion yuan, an increase of 42 percent over the previous year. 
  In rural economic development, the problem of unsynchronized 
growth of agricultural production and the increase in peasants' 
income remained. 
<H5>  II. Industry and the Building Industry </H5>
  In 1993, industrial enterprises in the whole region overcame 
unfavorable factors, such as a funds shortage, a drastic 
increase in the prices of raw and processed materials, and the 
inadequate transport capacity. With the market as a guide, they 
readjusted the product mix, increased scientific and 
technological input, and vigorously developed the work of 
technological transformation and of tapping potential and 
reducing consumption, which enabled industry to maintain a 
momentum of sustained, healthy, and high-speed development. In 
1993, the region's total industrial output, including industry 
of the village level and below, broke the 10-billion-yuan record 
for the first time, and reached 12.08 billion yuan, an increase 
of 13.9 percent over 1992. In total industrial output, the 
output of the township level and above reached 11.28 billion 
yuan, up 12.1 percent. In total industrial output of the 
township level and above, heavy industrial output amounted to 
9.17 billion yuan, up 15.4 percent; and light industrial output 
amounted to 2.11 billion yuan, up 1.8 percent. Divided by 
economic types, state-owned industry amounted to 9.41 billion 
yuan, up 9.5 percent; and collective industry amounted to 1.68 
billion yuan, up 20 percent, of which township-run industry 
amounted to 690 million yuan, up 44 percent. 



